Privacy Policy for Naam
Last Updated: January 25th, 2025
1. Introduction
This Privacy Policy explains how Georgy Bugakov (DBA Werknaam) (“we”, “us”, “our”) collects, uses, and protects your personal data when you use the Naam app (the “Service”).
2. Data Controller
For the purposes of the GDPR, we are the data controller and can be contacted at:
Email:
privacy@werknaam.be
Address: available upon request by email
3. Personal Data We Collect
We do not collect any personal data.
4. Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy occasionally. We will notify you of any material changes by:
Posting the new Privacy Policy on our website
Updating the “Last Updated” date
5. Data Protection Complaints
If you have concerns about our data processing, please contact us first. You also have the right to file a complaint with the Belgian Data Protection Authority:
Gegevensbeschermingsautoriteit
Drukpersstraat 35, 1000 Brussel
+32 (0)2 274 48 00
contact@apd-gba.be
https://www.gegevensbeschermingsautoriteit.be/burger/acties/contact
6. Contact Us
For any privacy-related questions or to exercise your rights, contact us at:
Email:
privacy@werknaam.be
Address: available upon request by email
Security reports:
security@werknaam.be
By using our Service, you acknowledge you have read and understood this Privacy Policy.